fields.description:
If the following warning log message is the expected cleanup workflow for ceph-rbd snapshots taken prior to 4.4 then we should verify that it contains all necessary information to perform cleanup and that the need to manually clean up snapshots is clearly documented: 

{code}
Cannot delete RBD snapshot for $SNAPSHOT_ID due to an invalid snapshot point ID $SNAPSHOT_POINT_ID. Either the EBS snapshot did not origniate in this az or was created pre Eucalyptus 4.4.0 in which case the cleanup of the RBD snapshot has to be performed manually
{code}

I'm not sure when this manual clean up is necessary.

comments.body:
After deleting a snapshot (snap-a02d9469) in 4.4 created from 4.3, I see this message:
{code}
Thu Jan 19 16:14:27 2017  WARN [CephRbdProvider:eucalyptus-storage-checkerthreadpool-worker-287] Cannot delete RBD snapshot for snap-a02d9469 due to an invalid snapshot point ID null. Either the EBS snapshot did not origniate in this az or was created pre Eucalyptus 4.4.0  in which case the cleanup of the RBD snapshot has to be performed manually
{code}

Example CLI command, on the host where the SC is running: (because that's where the rbd CLI is installed)

{noformat}
rbd --id qauser --keyring /etc/ceph/ceph.client.qauser.keyring snap rm eucaqa_vol/vol-72ea8b83@snap-f36046f5
{noformat}
